title: Faq Tariffs And Services En
text:
None
1. General Questions Q1: Why does the bank charge account maintenance fees? They cover the cost of managing your account, providing secure digital access, and processing transactions. Q2: Are there accounts without maintenance fees? Yes. The Youth Account (18–25) and Savings Accounts are free of monthly maintenance fees. Q3: How will I know if fees change? FinSight publishes all tariff updates 30 days before they take effect, online and in branches.

title: Faq Tariffs And Services En
text:
None
2. Cards and Withdrawals Q4: What are the annual fees for FinSight cards? Visa Classic 45 TND, Visa Gold 90 TND, Visa Platinum 150 TND, Visa Business 120 TND. Q5: Are withdrawals free at all ATMs? Free at FinSight ATMs; interbank withdrawals cost 1.5 TND. Q6: What should I do if my card is lost or stolen? Block via FinSight Mobile “Block Card” or call 71 000 123. Replacement free if theft with police report.

title: Faq Tariffs And Services En
text:
None
3. Transfers and Payments Q7: How much does a domestic transfer cost? Standard transfer 2 TND; inter-branch within FinSight free. Q8: What are international transfer fees? 0.15% of the amount (min 30 TND, max 300 TND). Q9: How long does it take to receive an international transfer? 1–3 working days depending on destination. Q10: Can I pay my bills online? Yes, through FinSight Online or FinSight Mobile for utilities, telecom, and taxes.

title: Faq Tariffs And Services En
text:
None
4. Overdrafts and Loans Q11: What is an overdraft facility? A short-term advance allowing a negative balance up to an authorized limit; interest applies only to usage. Q12: How is loan interest calculated? Based on Money Market Average Rate (TMM) plus a contractual margin. Q13: Can I repay my loan early? Yes, at any time. Fixed-rate loans may include a small compensation fee.

title: Faq Tariffs And Services En
text:
None
5. Digital Banking and Security Q14: Is FinSight Online secure? Yes. It uses encryption, one-time passwords (OTP), and session timeouts. Q15: Can I change daily transfer limits? Yes, via FinSight Mobile → Settings → Transfer Limits. Q16: What if I notice a suspicious transaction? Contact Customer Service at 71 000 123 for investigation and refund if unauthorized.

title: Faq Tariffs And Services En
text:
None
6. Support and Contact Q17: How can I contact the bank for more information? Call +216 71 000 123, email support@finsightbank.tn, or visit www.finsightbank.tn. Q18: Where can I find the full tariff brochure? Available under “Transparence tarifaire” on the FinSight website.
